Over.

276
00:16:04.030 --> 00:16:04.890
Mike. come on.

277
00:16:05.490 --> 00:16:07.650
Is that a police scanner you got?

278
00:16:08.090 --> 00:16:09.190
You keeping tabs on me?

279
00:16:09.530 --> 00:16:10.390
Yes. sir.

280
00:16:10.390 --> 00:16:12.650
And a CD radio.

281
00:16:12.970 --> 00:16:15.290
Oh. I get lonely.

282
00:16:15.950 --> 00:16:16.630
And nosy.

283
00:16:17.570 --> 00:16:18.390
Copy that. Sally.

284
00:16:18.470 --> 00:16:19.050
I'm on my way.

285
00:16:19.310 --> 00:16:19.810
Take care.

286
00:16:22.190 --> 00:16:24.150
Call the fire department next time.

287
00:16:25.050 --> 00:16:26.090
Oh. I...

288
00:16:26.090 --> 00:16:26.790
I'm kidding.

289
00:16:32.520 --> 00:16:35.260
Your buck goes a lot further out here. that's for sure.

290
00:16:35.860 --> 00:16:38.920
Gunderson had got himself the Big Mac of McMansions.

291
00:16:39.320 --> 00:16:42.140
He must have issued a hell of a lot of parking tickets to get that.

292
00:16:42.540 --> 00:16:45.000
So. what do you say about a man like Gunderson?

293
00:16:45.140 --> 00:16:47.100
He was a son of a bitch.

294
00:16:47.640 --> 00:16:49.480
But he was our son of a bitch.

295
00:16:49.880 --> 00:16:51.400
He was a great golfer.

296
00:16:51.780 --> 00:16:53.640
A medium fisherman.

297
00:16:54.480 --> 00:16:55.100
What's up?

298
00:16:55.880 --> 00:16:57.340
You gotta get in on this.

299
00:16:57.980 --> 00:16:59.760
This is just like Christmas.

300
00:17:00.460 --> 00:17:02.100
You got Pete's Meats.

301
00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:03.800
Fortune cookies.

302
00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:04.560
All you can eat.

303
00:17:04.900 --> 00:17:06.099
You want me to make you a plate?

304
00:17:07.800 --> 00:17:10.260
Not unless I want to end up like Gunderson.

305
00:17:10.720 --> 00:17:11.859
That reminds me.

306
00:17:14.930 --> 00:17:16.730
I think you should be wearing this.

307
00:17:18.810 --> 00:17:20.750
But I thought you said you had only one.

308
00:17:21.010 --> 00:17:21.410
I did.

309
00:17:21.849 --> 00:17:25.928
But when the citation was over and done with ...

310
00:17:25.928 --> 00:17:32.130
 I nicked it off of the courts before they closed the casket.

311
00:17:32.510 --> 00:17:35.630
So. you enjoy the power while it lasts.

312
00:18:02.290 --> 00:18:03.930
Oh. what a trip that was.

313
00:18:04.590 --> 00:18:06.350
Japanese sure love their golf.

314
00:18:08.790 --> 00:18:09.670
So?

315
00:18:10.470 --> 00:18:11.690
What'd you pick?

316
00:18:12.670 --> 00:18:14.390
Oh. uh. Ashford something.

317
00:18:14.990 --> 00:18:19.110
I always tend to lean toward the Irish.

318
00:18:19.830 --> 00:18:21.290
Seven G's a bottle.

319
00:18:24.290 --> 00:18:25.570
Dr. Belay.

320
00:18:26.070 --> 00:18:26.730
Ulysses.

321
00:18:27.590 --> 00:18:32.930
Um. you signed Sheriff Gunderson's death certificate. right?

322
00:18:33.610 --> 00:18:35.570
Sadly. yes. I did.

323
00:18:35.570 --> 00:18:37.290
What happened there?

324
00:18:39.050 --> 00:18:42.210
Well. a couple Wednesdays ago. around three in the morning. 

325
00:18:42.210 --> 00:18:46.040
Deputy Blaine found him out back in little more than his tighty-whities. 

326
00:18:46.070 --> 00:18:50.450
frozen like a chunk of ice chiseled by a chainsaw.

327
00:18:51.190 --> 00:18:52.830
What do you suppose he thought he was doing?

328
00:18:54.410 --> 00:18:56.930
My job goes to posing to be sure.

329
00:18:57.990 --> 00:18:59.130
Gunderson likes his fishing.

330
00:18:59.330 --> 00:19:07.430
He had a fishing rod in his one hand and an auger in the other. so my guess. the man thought he was going ice fishing.

331
00:19:08.290 --> 00:19:09.010
At night?

332
00:19:09.410 --> 00:19:10.350
In his underwear?

333
00:19:11.750 --> 00:19:14.090
Well. as you can see. the man was a drinker.

334
00:19:14.870 --> 00:19:16.090
And a son of a bitch.

335
00:19:16.650 --> 00:19:19.170
Well. then again. he was our son of a bitch. right?

336
00:19:19.930 --> 00:19:21.050
Hey. Doc. give me a minute.

337
00:19:21.170 --> 00:19:22.470
I'd like to bend his ear. okay?

338
00:19:23.290 --> 00:19:24.050
Yeah. yeah.

339
00:19:24.970 --> 00:19:26.850
I want to thank you for coming.

340
00:19:27.550 --> 00:19:28.150
Of course.

341
00:19:28.850 --> 00:19:30.270
So let me get this straight.

342
00:19:31.010 --> 00:19:36.470
Did I hear you saw the moose?

343
00:19:36.710 --> 00:19:37.310
I did.

344
00:19:37.630 --> 00:19:38.910
I got a picture of it.

345
00:19:39.230 --> 00:19:39.710
Goddamn!

346
00:19:40.210 --> 00:19:43.510
I am the only one in this town who has never seen that fucking moose.

347
00:19:43.910 --> 00:19:45.830
And I keep an eye out for it.

348
00:19:46.410 --> 00:19:51.190
You know. in Native American culture. the moose is a symbol of endurance and survival.

349
00:19:51.970 --> 00:19:52.070
Hmm?

350
00:19:53.910 --> 00:19:57.170
So. what do you think of our little town?

351
00:19:58.650 --> 00:19:59.750
It's. um. charming.

352
00:20:00.070 --> 00:20:00.290
Yeah.

353
00:20:00.290 --> 00:20:04.550
You know. I hear that you are a very laid-back kind of guy.

354
00:20:04.870 --> 00:20:06.790
Not a crack-the-whip sort.

355
00:20:07.870 --> 00:20:09.610
Well. I mean. I've been known to...

356
00:20:09.610 --> 00:20:10.950
Do you ever think about settling down?

357
00:20:12.370 --> 00:20:15.590
You could be a real sheriff for more than a few weeks.

358
00:20:16.370 --> 00:20:18.550
You could build a whole new life here in Normal.

359
00:20:19.310 --> 00:20:22.950
Because we really celebrate the community.

360
00:20:23.650 --> 00:20:26.390
Around here. it's always one for all.

361
00:20:27.470 --> 00:20:28.590
That sounds...

362
00:20:28.590 --> 00:20:28.830
Mayor?

363
00:20:28.830 --> 00:20:29.110
Yeah.

364
00:20:29.230 --> 00:20:29.670
It's time.

365
00:20:29.890 --> 00:20:30.050
Yeah.

366
00:20:31.070 --> 00:20:32.550
But I want you to think about it.

367
00:20:32.910 --> 00:20:33.270
I will.

368
00:20:33.530 --> 00:20:33.890
All right.

369
00:20:43.160 --> 00:20:43.600
Hi.

370
00:20:55.780 --> 00:20:56.300
Hey. boss.

371
00:20:58.000 --> 00:20:59.920
I was just checking on you.

372
00:21:00.960 --> 00:21:01.680
You good?

373
00:21:02.080 --> 00:21:03.040
I'm fine.

374
00:21:03.480 --> 00:21:07.140
Well. I just wanted to let you know that they put out more of those mini egg rolls.

375
00:21:07.220 --> 00:21:07.720
They're custom.

376
00:21:08.880 --> 00:21:13.500
And the mayor's just about to tell the story about the time he went on the cruise with Jane Fonda. so...

377
00:21:16.680 --> 00:21:18.180
You know who that is in the van?

378
00:21:19.600 --> 00:21:22.560
Sheriff Gunderson's daughter. I think.

379
00:21:23.380 --> 00:21:23.940
Alex.

380
00:21:34.920 --> 00:21:36.280
You're a ball man.

381
00:21:37.360 --> 00:21:37.940
Is that for a game?

382
00:21:39.140 --> 00:21:40.480
My hands are shaky.

383
00:21:40.780 --> 00:21:42.060
They only trust me with a gun.

384
00:21:43.760 --> 00:21:44.480
Company. then?

385
00:21:46.080 --> 00:21:46.980
I gotta warn you.

386
00:21:47.860 --> 00:21:48.980
Not very good.

387
00:21:49.820 --> 00:21:51.620
So would you say you knew Gunderson well?

388
00:21:52.080 --> 00:21:52.520
Gunderson?

389
00:21:52.680 --> 00:21:52.880
Yeah.

390
00:21:53.160 --> 00:21:54.160
I knew him pretty well.

391
00:21:55.380 --> 00:21:57.420
He was sad. the way he are.

392
00:21:59.320 --> 00:21:59.760
Yeah.

393
00:22:00.700 --> 00:22:01.740
But he liked to drink.

394
00:22:02.020 --> 00:22:05.140
He liked to fish. so the way I see it. he died doing what he loved best.

395
00:22:06.040 --> 00:22:06.620
You fish?

396
00:22:07.920 --> 00:22:09.820
When I was a kid. with my dad.

397
00:22:10.640 --> 00:22:10.860
You?

398
00:22:10.860 --> 00:22:11.640
Me?

399
00:22:11.740 --> 00:22:12.280
Fuck. no.

400
00:22:13.060 --> 00:22:14.660
Probably the only one in town who don't.

401
00:22:15.280 --> 00:22:18.480
But in the end. death comes for us all.

402
00:22:18.580 --> 00:22:19.320
Don't alone. man.

403
00:22:20.760 --> 00:22:22.920
Unlike getting a sheriff out of you. huh?

404
00:22:23.680 --> 00:22:25.420
If you really were. you would.

405
00:22:25.460 --> 00:22:26.100
But are you?

406
00:22:29.780 --> 00:22:32.460
You've been listening to my internal monologue. haven't you?

407
00:22:33.100 --> 00:22:34.100
It's my job.

408
00:22:36.220 --> 00:22:38.380
I'm Moira. the barkeeper here.

409
00:22:41.720 --> 00:22:42.460
Rack him up.

410
00:22:43.300 --> 00:22:44.280
Why are you here?

411
00:22:44.720 --> 00:22:46.260
Stop fucking around. come on.

412
00:22:47.500 --> 00:22:48.420
I'm all ears.

413
00:22:49.420 --> 00:22:49.760
All right.

414
00:22:52.380 --> 00:22:54.460
I used to be a regular sheriff.

415
00:22:55.180 --> 00:22:58.540
Nice county with a couple little towns just like this one.

416
00:22:59.180 --> 00:23:00.740
Then married my high school sweetheart.

417
00:23:01.980 --> 00:23:02.540
Perfect.

418
00:23:03.180 --> 00:23:03.840
It was.

419
00:23:04.300 --> 00:23:08.480
I was. uh. pretty proud of myself.

420
00:23:09.580 --> 00:23:12.120
I walked through life with my head held high.

421
00:23:12.120 --> 00:23:14.240
I knew who I was.

422
00:23:19.330 --> 00:23:24.850
And this girl. uh. her dad was someone I knew.

423
00:23:25.770 --> 00:23:27.930
A. uh. upstanding citizen.

424
00:23:30.750 --> 00:23:32.433
Had been. uh. 

425
00:23:38.003 --> 00:23:39.681
I didn't believe her.

426
00:23:41.860 --> 00:23:45.160
Short while later. there was an incident at the house.

427
00:23:47.260 --> 00:23:47.590
Gunshots.

428
00:23:48.600 --> 00:23:53.060
And I went in and she was standing over him.

429
00:23:54.040 --> 00:23:55.000
He was wounded.

430
00:23:55.980 --> 00:24:02.560
She had a gun out and he was cursing her for what he'd done to her.

431
00:24:04.440 --> 00:24:07.680
And I told her to put the gun down and she didn't hesitate.

432
00:24:07.960 --> 00:24:09.660
She shot him right between the eyes.

433
00:24:10.940 --> 00:24:12.280
And then she aimed that gun at me.

434
00:24:13.780 --> 00:24:15.900
She cursed me for not believing her.

435
00:24:19.980 --> 00:24:21.680
And then we both shot.

436
00:24:25.780 --> 00:24:27.100
And I had better aim.

437
00:24:31.080 --> 00:24:32.648
After that.

438
00:24:35.499 --> 00:24:37.534
 I got dark inside and ...

439
00:24:40.800 --> 00:24:43.380
 I didn't know who I was anymore and I still don't.

440
00:24:48.980 --> 00:24:49.680
And the wife?

441
00:24:51.540 --> 00:24:51.960
Yeah.

442
00:24:52.340 --> 00:24:53.560
It was hard to be around.

443
00:24:54.840 --> 00:24:56.180
I still call her.

444
00:24:59.380 --> 00:25:00.420
She doesn't answer.

445
00:25:00.700 --> 00:25:03.020
But I don't mind.

446
00:25:04.660 --> 00:25:06.620
I live in hope one day she will.

447
00:25:26.110 --> 00:25:27.350
Sheriff. to the mayor.

448
00:25:27.870 --> 00:25:29.830
People are really liking your light touch.

449
00:25:30.090 --> 00:25:31.710
Have you considered my offer?

450
00:25:32.290 --> 00:25:33.470
Get back to me as soon as you can.

451
00:25:33.490 --> 00:25:36.470
What a stupid phone you got.

452
00:25:36.910 --> 00:25:38.690
I bet I can help you with that.

453
00:25:39.230 --> 00:25:40.850
Oh. hi. officer.

454
00:25:41.110 --> 00:25:41.310
Hey.

455
00:25:41.310 --> 00:25:44.070
Sheriff. I got stuck.

456
00:25:44.190 --> 00:25:44.990
Yeah. I see.

457
00:25:45.950 --> 00:25:47.470
What do you think will knock it down?

458
00:25:47.770 --> 00:25:48.990
The caramel or the cookie?

459
00:25:49.510 --> 00:25:51.010
It's not caramel sugar.

460
00:25:51.450 --> 00:25:52.810
Yeah. that's my guess too.

461
00:25:55.190 --> 00:25:56.390
What's your dog's name?

462
00:25:56.650 --> 00:25:57.470
Oh. her name's Olive.

463
00:25:58.910 --> 00:25:59.430
Nice.

464
00:25:59.510 --> 00:25:59.890
Yeah.

465
00:26:00.490 --> 00:26:01.230
Hey. Olive.

466
00:26:02.050 --> 00:26:03.470
What a good dog.

467
00:26:04.090 --> 00:26:05.250
My name's Ulysses.

468
00:26:06.030 --> 00:26:06.910
I'm Lori.

469
00:26:08.830 --> 00:26:10.470
You know. I wish these things had dog food.

470
00:26:12.470 --> 00:26:14.190
Yeah. well. someday.

471
00:26:14.530 --> 00:26:14.650
Yeah.

472
00:26:16.090 --> 00:26:18.710
All right. well. watch out for the moose.

473
00:26:19.570 --> 00:26:20.170
Moose?

474
00:26:20.570 --> 00:26:20.930
Yeah.

475
00:26:21.910 --> 00:26:22.350
Big.

476
00:26:22.990 --> 00:26:24.630
Careful. he might try and paint you.

477
00:26:25.390 --> 00:26:26.070
Moose?

478
00:26:40.280 --> 00:26:40.960
Yeah?

479
00:26:47.610 --> 00:26:48.290
Thanks.

480
00:26:49.670 --> 00:26:59.330
Look. I hate I don't know if I should say this. but our mustaches are so similar.

481
00:27:01.170 --> 00:27:02.370
Like a couple brothers.

482
00:27:03.490 --> 00:27:05.070
Or at least a couple uncles.

483
00:27:08.870 --> 00:27:10.850
Well. I should probably get back at it.

484
00:27:27.190 --> 00:27:29.370
How can love go away?

485
00:27:30.650 --> 00:27:31.630
Did I take it for granted?

486
00:27:32.050 --> 00:27:33.150
I guess I did.

487
00:27:33.670 --> 00:27:37.430
I didn't protect that girl and I lost you in the bargain.

488
00:27:38.490 --> 00:27:40.430
You said I shut down Penny.

489
00:27:40.730 --> 00:27:41.410
You were right.

490
00:27:45.560 --> 00:27:47.260
Is this what happened to Gunderson?

491
00:27:48.120 --> 00:27:49.640
Did he give up?

492
00:27:49.840 --> 00:27:50.720
Say fuck it?

493
00:27:51.420 --> 00:27:52.960
Walk into the snow buck naked?

494
00:27:54.400 --> 00:27:56.040
Oh. that's a hell of a way to die.

495
00:27:58.320 --> 00:28:00.080
I'm not doing anything wrong.

496
00:28:01.180 --> 00:28:02.300
You been drinking?

497
00:28:05.520 --> 00:28:08.440
No. when I was driving and I pulled off to the store.

498
00:28:11.300 --> 00:28:11.920
Bourbon?

499
00:28:16.980 --> 00:28:18.000
It's very impressive.

500
00:28:18.740 --> 00:28:19.720
You mind if I join you?

501
00:28:21.220 --> 00:28:22.340
I'd join.

502
00:28:34.290 --> 00:28:35.670
That's a cool belt.

503
00:28:38.800 --> 00:28:39.620
I'm Alex.

504
00:28:40.600 --> 00:28:41.480
I'm Ulysses.

505
00:28:42.680 --> 00:28:44.800
Can I have the cheap booze?

506
00:28:49.670 --> 00:28:51.470
You're Gunderson's daughter. right?

507
00:28:54.330 --> 00:28:54.750
No.

508
00:28:56.450 --> 00:28:56.910
Oh.

509
00:28:58.730 --> 00:28:59.530
Yeah. okay.

510
00:29:00.050 --> 00:29:02.050
You're Gunderson's kid.

511
00:29:03.130 --> 00:29:03.430
Yeah.

512
00:29:03.690 --> 00:29:06.030
Lots of pictures of you on the wall in his office.

513
00:29:06.810 --> 00:29:07.610
You got his eyes.

514
00:29:09.370 --> 00:29:10.010
Yeah.

515
00:29:10.670 --> 00:29:12.190
Those are old pictures.

516
00:29:14.390 --> 00:29:15.890
He's very proud of me.

517
00:29:16.930 --> 00:29:19.110
Daddy's little girl going military.

518
00:29:19.930 --> 00:29:20.870
Couldn't keep that up.

519
00:29:24.090 --> 00:29:27.550
You were having an argument with Deputy Blaine outside the house.

520
00:29:27.650 --> 00:29:28.490
What was that about?

521
00:29:29.950 --> 00:29:36.704
The mayor. he didn't want me to attend the memorial service because ...

522
00:29:36.704 --> 00:29:40.950
he said that I would be too much of a distraction.

523
00:29:42.590 --> 00:29:43.550
Oh. fuck the mayor.

524
00:29:44.610 --> 00:29:45.210
Yeah.

525
00:29:45.750 --> 00:29:50.431
The town used to know right from wrong before Mayor Kidman got here and ..

526
00:29:50.431 --> 00:29:55.813
tried to make my dad see that but he was stuck between me and the town.

527
00:29:58.450 --> 00:29:58.870
Yeah.

528
00:30:06.150 --> 00:30:07.189
He killed him.

529
00:30:08.510 --> 00:30:10.250
And I don't know what to do.

530
00:30:12.860 --> 00:30:13.960
Neither do I.

531
00:30:15.540 --> 00:30:17.820
But I got an idea where we could start.

532
00:30:18.300 --> 00:30:19.380
You wanna give me that?

533
00:30:28.280 --> 00:30:29.480
Did you catch that?

534
00:30:30.720 --> 00:30:32.220
Yeah. it's my one trick.

535
00:30:36.620 --> 00:30:37.660
How long you been awake?

536
00:30:38.440 --> 00:30:39.620
That's a great question.

537
00:30:40.800 --> 00:30:42.600
I got a place you can crash.

538
00:30:43.380 --> 00:30:44.280
It's a safe place.

539
00:30:45.300 --> 00:30:47.620
It's the safest place in town.

540
00:30:55.830 --> 00:30:56.470
You're serious?

541
00:30:57.310 --> 00:30:57.810
Yeah.

542
00:30:58.390 --> 00:30:59.150
Hilarious.

543
00:31:00.430 --> 00:31:01.970
Breakfast is included.

544
00:31:03.510 --> 00:31:04.910
I didn't get you anything else?

545
00:31:06.670 --> 00:31:07.730
Lock the door.

546
00:31:10.250 --> 00:31:11.010
Sure.

547
00:31:15.810 --> 00:31:17.350
I'll be in my office.

548
00:31:17.550 --> 00:31:18.470
Just yell.

549
00:31:19.650 --> 00:31:22.750
Either be sleeping or drinking.

550
00:31:24.110 --> 00:31:25.110
Can I?

551
00:31:31.610 --> 00:31:33.030
It's gonna run like clockwork.

552
00:31:35.050 --> 00:31:35.510
Where?

553
00:31:36.190 --> 00:31:37.810
You okay?

554
00:31:38.610 --> 00:31:38.790
Yeah.

555
00:31:58.250 --> 00:32:01.110
