925
00:51:42.190 --> 00:51:44.430
Ice for this severed ear. Kenny.

926
00:51:44.690 --> 00:51:46.830
So. what's with all these nights on commotion?

927
00:51:47.170 --> 00:51:53.450
You know. a pair of bank robbers. they decided to team up with the sheriff after they discovered that he threw the gold in our vault.

928
00:51:54.370 --> 00:51:56.170
And they blew up the mayor. Kenny.

929
00:51:56.930 --> 00:51:58.070
He's on my face.

930
00:51:58.490 --> 00:51:59.510
It was really gross.

931
00:51:59.790 --> 00:52:00.690
Oh. shit.

932
00:52:00.930 --> 00:52:03.410
Oyabun is coming to kill us all.

933
00:52:04.330 --> 00:52:05.510
You have your devil.

934
00:52:06.110 --> 00:52:07.930
We have our akuma.

935
00:52:08.790 --> 00:52:10.250
Both fear Oyabun.

936
00:52:10.930 --> 00:52:16.390
Look. the way I figure it. with the power down. they can't get the word out.

937
00:52:16.870 --> 00:52:21.530
And with the storm being what it is. they're stuck here with us.

938
00:52:21.530 --> 00:52:26.910
And. you know. better to be the hunter than the hunted.

939
00:52:28.430 --> 00:52:28.930
Right?

940
00:52:29.550 --> 00:52:29.910
Yeah.

941
00:52:30.190 --> 00:52:30.530
Yes.

942
00:52:31.030 --> 00:52:32.290
So. who's up for an affogato?

943
00:52:33.470 --> 00:52:34.270
On the house.

944
00:52:36.770 --> 00:52:37.610
Open that.

945
00:52:39.350 --> 00:52:40.330
Oh. God.

946
00:52:40.530 --> 00:52:41.250
Need some tape.

947
00:52:41.550 --> 00:52:42.090
Where's Olive?

948
00:52:42.310 --> 00:52:43.470
She's in the car. sweetheart.

949
00:52:43.870 --> 00:52:45.230
We left the heater on. remember?

950
00:52:46.110 --> 00:52:49.710
So. it's just us three versus this entire whack-ass town?

951
00:52:49.710 --> 00:52:52.790
Well. usually when you rob a bank. there are consequences.

952
00:52:53.590 --> 00:52:55.370
Although this. this is a new one.

953
00:52:56.670 --> 00:52:58.230
We just wanted something.

954
00:52:59.130 --> 00:53:02.310
If we get through whatever the fuck this is. that'll be something.

955
00:53:04.270 --> 00:53:05.490
Okay. what's the plan?

956
00:53:06.210 --> 00:53:08.470
We're gonna go to the police station.

957
00:53:09.010 --> 00:53:10.110
They got a snowplow there.

958
00:53:10.570 --> 00:53:11.870
We'll get the fuck out of Dodge.

959
00:53:12.270 --> 00:53:12.650
Okay.

960
00:53:13.530 --> 00:53:14.730
I can drive a snowplow.

961
00:53:15.570 --> 00:53:16.490
You're the man.

962
00:53:16.590 --> 00:53:17.010
Let's go.

963
00:53:17.330 --> 00:53:17.910
Let's go.

964
00:53:20.930 --> 00:53:22.270
Come on. Mr. Plow.

965
00:53:34.230 --> 00:53:34.750
Go!

966
00:53:36.050 --> 00:53:36.430
Go!

967
00:53:36.950 --> 00:53:37.730
I'm okay.

968
00:53:37.850 --> 00:53:38.550
He has a vest.

969
00:53:38.930 --> 00:53:39.930
Get out of here!

970
00:53:40.130 --> 00:53:41.590
We'll meet at the police station!

971
00:53:59.090 --> 00:54:00.130
Hello. Sheriff.

972
00:54:01.010 --> 00:54:01.690
Eat bone!

973
00:54:28.130 --> 00:54:31.276
You're a slippery little fishy H.I. 

974
00:54:36.938 --> 00:54:38.790
God dammit. Stay down.

975
00:54:42.680 --> 00:54:43.880
What the hell. man?

976
00:54:44.260 --> 00:54:45.900
What is wrong with you people?

977
00:54:45.960 --> 00:54:50.160
We're looking up and we chose you because of your reputation for not giving a shit.

978
00:54:50.680 --> 00:54:52.200
Why'd you decide to start now?

979
00:54:53.300 --> 00:54:54.540
I'm not myself lately.

980
00:55:10.570 --> 00:55:11.510
Goddamn!

981
00:55:30.180 --> 00:55:30.480
Huh?

982
00:55:30.880 --> 00:55:33.000
Old-fashioned stump removers.

983
00:55:53.201 --> 00:55:54.963
Is that a mail man ?

984
00:55:57.768 --> 00:55:59.410
You stole a gold brick?

985
00:56:00.810 --> 00:56:01.950
Of course I did.

986
00:56:18.670 --> 00:56:18.770
Ah!

987
00:56:49.080 --> 00:56:50.180
Physics. bitch.

988
00:56:51.740 --> 00:56:55.580
Uh. is he okay?

989
00:56:56.060 --> 00:56:57.860
Um. no.

990
00:56:59.800 --> 00:57:00.520
Go!

991
00:57:05.200 --> 00:57:06.380
Hold your fire!

992
00:57:06.440 --> 00:57:07.120
Hold your fire!

993
00:57:14.340 --> 00:57:15.720
They murdered James.

994
00:57:17.360 --> 00:57:18.880
They murdered our mailman.

995
00:57:20.100 --> 00:57:22.160
Oh. what fresh hell is this?

996
00:57:22.380 --> 00:57:24.060
Oh. be careful with that. Father.

997
00:57:25.120 --> 00:57:26.340
It's only a flare.

998
00:57:28.640 --> 00:57:29.580
Hey. there's another one.

999
00:57:30.380 --> 00:57:30.700
It's okay.

1000
00:57:31.060 --> 00:57:31.460
Ah!

1001
00:57:36.640 --> 00:57:37.140
Clean!

1002
00:57:38.660 --> 00:57:39.160
Father!

1003
00:57:39.380 --> 00:57:40.620
Go. go. go. go. go. go. go. go!

1004
00:57:40.820 --> 00:57:41.060
Mike!

1005
00:57:41.060 --> 00:57:42.160
I got it. I got it. I got it.

1006
00:57:42.240 --> 00:57:43.140
Mike. I got it.

1007
00:57:43.200 --> 00:57:44.060
What are you doing. Mike?

1008
00:57:45.020 --> 00:57:45.460
Goddamn!

1009
00:57:51.720 --> 00:57:52.940
Bentley. I'm a hero.

1010
00:57:57.100 --> 00:57:57.540
Mike!

1011
00:57:58.840 --> 00:57:59.900
Oh. he's gone.

1012
00:58:27.770 --> 00:58:28.210
Nice.

1013
00:58:31.050 --> 00:58:31.830
Put him up.

1014
00:58:37.030 --> 00:58:37.830
Did you talk?

1015
00:58:37.990 --> 00:58:38.410
Some of ya.

1016
00:58:41.250 --> 00:58:41.830
You did.

1017
00:59:06.890 --> 00:59:08.610
I thought you knew how to drive one of these.

1018
00:59:08.790 --> 00:59:09.510
Yeah. I do.

1019
00:59:10.550 --> 00:59:11.270
Yeah. you know.

1020
00:59:12.010 --> 00:59:12.370
I do.

1021
00:59:14.260 --> 00:59:14.700
I did.

1022
00:59:14.960 --> 00:59:16.920
I just. I just. I can't.

1023
00:59:18.540 --> 00:59:21.780
Remember when you said you could drive a train?

1024
00:59:22.220 --> 00:59:23.380
And that was bullshit. too.

1025
00:59:25.460 --> 00:59:25.840
Yeah.

1026
00:59:26.060 --> 00:59:26.260
Ah.

1027
00:59:27.060 --> 00:59:27.440
See?

1028
00:59:27.600 --> 00:59:27.800
Yeah.

1029
00:59:27.800 --> 00:59:27.900
Yeah.

1030
00:59:45.000 --> 00:59:45.460
Hey.

1031
00:59:57.300 --> 00:59:57.560
Go!

1032
00:59:58.160 --> 00:59:58.920
Oh. my.

1033
01:00:00.280 --> 01:00:00.960
I should have knocked.

1034
01:00:01.760 --> 01:00:02.940
Can you drive this thing?

1035
01:00:04.320 --> 01:00:05.340
Yeah. I think so.

1036
01:00:05.760 --> 01:00:07.020
Okay. we'll get to a hospital.

1037
01:00:07.220 --> 01:00:08.100
You're not coming with us?

1038
01:00:08.220 --> 01:00:09.740
No. I'm sticking around.

1039
01:00:10.780 --> 01:00:13.640
I'm tired of running away from every goddamn thing.

1040
01:00:14.520 --> 01:00:16.460
And you consider this your second chance?

1041
01:00:17.060 --> 01:00:18.880
You take that gold brick. eh?

1042
01:00:20.420 --> 01:00:22.320
Then go build something good out of it.

1043
01:00:22.920 --> 01:00:24.120
Take care of yourselves.

1044
01:00:42.320 --> 01:00:45.040
How do we even sell a gold brick?

1045
01:00:45.900 --> 01:00:46.880
Break it in half?

1046
01:00:46.880 --> 01:00:48.740
Well. I'm stuck.

1047
01:00:57.240 --> 01:00:57.900
Damn it.

1048
01:00:58.300 --> 01:00:59.140
Where could they have gone?

1049
01:00:59.760 --> 01:01:00.600
It's a small town.

1050
01:01:03.599 --> 01:01:04.480
That's our cloud.

1051
01:01:05.020 --> 01:01:06.000
That ain't Ulysses.

1052
01:01:06.460 --> 01:01:07.420
He ain't the right type.

1053
01:01:07.500 --> 01:01:08.680
Well. where is he gonna hide?

1054
01:01:09.480 --> 01:01:10.560
The police station.

1055
01:01:11.540 --> 01:01:12.140
Let's get him.

1056
01:01:36.380 --> 01:01:37.980
Come on.

1057
01:01:41.180 --> 01:01:42.200
Let's go.

1058
01:01:52.300 --> 01:01:53.700
Let's go home.

1059
01:01:55.160 --> 01:01:56.160
Yeah. I love you.

1060
01:01:56.520 --> 01:01:57.560
Fuck this place.

1061
01:02:29.040 --> 01:02:30.160
Hey. little man.

1062
01:02:33.530 --> 01:02:36.310
You don't have to have a drink on you. do you?

1063
01:02:37.010 --> 01:02:40.550
What kind of bartender would I be if I didn't?

1064
01:02:42.810 --> 01:02:43.430
Let's trade.

1065
01:02:50.730 --> 01:02:51.770
Fuckin' slowly.

1066
01:03:10.540 --> 01:03:11.860
Well. drink up.

1067
01:03:14.250 --> 01:03:19.910
So we can all clean up this mess you made before the Yakuza turn up and kill every single one of us.

1068
01:03:20.110 --> 01:03:20.850
You too. huh?

1069
01:03:22.030 --> 01:03:24.190
Just doing what I need to do to survive.

1070
01:03:24.850 --> 01:03:25.770
At what cost?

1071
01:03:28.050 --> 01:03:28.730
My soul.

1072
01:03:30.510 --> 01:03:32.070
Although they're cheap nowadays.

1073
01:03:32.210 --> 01:03:33.830
Hell. you sold yours. didn't you?

1074
01:03:34.830 --> 01:03:36.230
I didn't sell mine.

1075
01:03:38.510 --> 01:03:39.670
I lost it.

1076
01:03:42.120 --> 01:03:43.060
How did you know?

1077
01:03:43.380 --> 01:03:44.800
Bartenders hear a lot of bullshit.

1078
01:03:46.920 --> 01:03:49.660
You get really good at sniffing out the lies.

1079
01:03:51.300 --> 01:03:55.460
Your story was true right until the end. am I right?

1080
01:03:59.740 --> 01:04:01.600
The girl didn't kill her dad.

1081
01:04:03.240 --> 01:04:04.040
You did.

1082
01:04:10.370 --> 01:04:11.290
I shot him.

1083
01:04:13.190 --> 01:04:16.070
Right between the eyes for what he'd done.

1084
01:04:20.920 --> 01:04:21.860
It was justice.

1085
01:04:24.640 --> 01:04:25.340
Now I don't know.

1086
01:04:26.720 --> 01:04:29.420
I've been avoiding making any choices since then.

1087
01:04:30.620 --> 01:04:33.500
Just watching life from the sidelines.

1088
01:04:34.280 --> 01:04:35.780
That's my truth.

1089
01:04:36.920 --> 01:04:37.900
Now you go.

1090
01:04:38.880 --> 01:04:39.840
What happened to Gunderson?

1091
01:04:39.840 --> 01:04:43.100
I already told that mean fish fuck no.

1092
01:04:43.920 --> 01:04:45.600
Probably the only one in town who don't.

1093
01:04:47.380 --> 01:04:52.500
Gunderson. he had a fishing pole in one hand. like this one. and an auger in the other.

1094
01:04:53.520 --> 01:04:55.640
So my guess is he thought he was going ice fishing.

1095
01:04:56.700 --> 01:04:59.080
Who the fuck goes ice fishing with a fly rod?

1096
01:04:59.620 --> 01:05:00.520
No one.

1097
01:05:02.480 --> 01:05:03.020
I lied.

1098
01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:04.580
I killed him.

1099
01:05:05.200 --> 01:05:07.220
Because he wanted a bigger cut of the deal?

1100
01:05:07.220 --> 01:05:08.420
Because he wanted out?

1101
01:05:09.280 --> 01:05:10.280
Of the job?

1102
01:05:10.520 --> 01:05:13.360
Of town?

1103
01:05:13.540 --> 01:05:14.080
The arrangement?

1104
01:05:14.900 --> 01:05:15.260
Why?

1105
01:05:17.680 --> 01:05:21.060
Because this kid. this town made him choose.

1106
01:05:22.160 --> 01:05:24.980
It's a small town in every way. you know?

1107
01:05:25.860 --> 01:05:26.640
Small minded.

1108
01:05:27.240 --> 01:05:28.420
Yeah. I get that.

1109
01:05:29.840 --> 01:05:31.640
And no one gets out.

1110
01:05:32.220 --> 01:05:33.120
Not even him.

1111
01:05:34.320 --> 01:05:39.480
So you got him drunk and walked him out and...

1112
01:05:39.480 --> 01:05:41.180
Watched him freeze to death.

1113
01:05:42.160 --> 01:05:45.500
Which takes longer than you'd think.

1114
01:05:46.280 --> 01:05:50.260
Unless you're wet. which he was because I poured water on him.

1115
01:05:51.100 --> 01:05:53.400
But I learned something about myself that night.

1116
01:05:54.720 --> 01:05:55.560
What's that?

1117
01:05:56.360 --> 01:05:58.200
That I can do what needs to be done.

1118
01:05:59.300 --> 01:06:00.620
What happened to you?

1119
01:06:01.180 --> 01:06:02.500
Nothing I didn't choose.

1120
01:06:05.120 --> 01:06:07.340
Like I said. that's a cool belt.

1121
01:06:15.280 --> 01:06:16.620
What the fuck. Sheriff?

1122
01:06:17.980 --> 01:06:19.240
Tell me about it.

1123
01:06:21.020 --> 01:06:25.360
I think he would have wanted you to have this. especially in light of current events.

1124
01:06:30.510 --> 01:06:32.110
Let's go. Deputy.

1125
01:06:32.110 --> 01:06:36.130
This shitstorm is only gonna get worse.

1126
01:07:25.620 --> 01:07:27.540
Did we leave anyone back at the bank?

1127
01:07:29.040 --> 01:07:29.600
No. Joe.

1128
01:07:30.940 --> 01:07:32.040
And the vault?

1129
01:07:33.320 --> 01:07:34.040
Yeah. Joe.

1130
01:07:35.360 --> 01:07:38.780
Is it still open?

1131
01:07:38.780 --> 01:07:39.020
No.

1132
01:08:09.097 --> 01:08:10.602
Answer the phone.

1133
01:08:12.338 --> 01:08:15.163
My dear penny is purely securing.

1134
01:08:15.410 --> 01:08:16.790
The contents of your vault.

1135
01:08:22.540 --> 01:08:23.480
Security.

1136
01:08:24.480 --> 01:08:32.559
Bricks of C4 have been planted in and amongst the Yakuza's physical deposits. as it were.

1137
01:08:34.860 --> 01:08:39.539
So. to sum up. if I die. it all goes boom.

1138
01:08:40.624 --> 01:08:48.518
If it goes boom. well then. the yakuza and all ... I don't think it'll end very well for you.

1139
01:08:49.399 --> 01:08:51.652
If we don't finish this here and now.

1140
01:08:51.852 --> 01:08:55.670
 the Yakuza will hunt down and kill each and every one of us.

1141
01:08:59.660 --> 01:09:01.480
But wait. there's more.

1142
01:09:03.760 --> 01:09:04.940
I've got a proposal.

1143
01:09:08.000 --> 01:09:13.460
We tidy up the bank. make it look like an accident. like nothing bad happened.

1144
01:09:14.920 --> 01:09:17.040
Just another Saturday.

1145
01:09:19.760 --> 01:09:23.380
Kenny. you say this is Belgian chocolate?

1146
01:09:23.740 --> 01:09:24.060
French.

1147
01:09:26.040 --> 01:09:27.640
Same difference. you know.

1148
01:09:30.240 --> 01:09:32.120
So. that's your plan?

1149
01:09:33.460 --> 01:09:34.020
That's it.

1150
01:09:35.900 --> 01:09:37.940
Just make it seem like any other day?

1151
01:09:38.300 --> 01:09:39.160
Basically. yeah.

1152
01:09:39.160 --> 01:09:44.280
If the Yakuza show up. their treasure is untouched.

1153
01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:47.760
Nothing more than a car accident that set off the alarm.

1154
01:09:48.300 --> 01:09:49.780
Life in normal is normal.

1155
01:09:50.360 --> 01:09:50.620
Calm.

1156
01:09:52.280 --> 01:09:52.840
Calm?

1157
01:09:54.680 --> 01:09:55.560
Queen's messy.

1158
01:09:56.600 --> 01:09:57.180
That's right.

1159
01:09:58.380 --> 01:10:02.860
Why don't I just kill you right now?

1160
01:10:05.020 --> 01:10:08.760
The only thing your boss is going to give a shit about is that you messed up.

1161
01:10:10.320 --> 01:10:13.380
And I say we play the hand that's been dealt to all of us.

1162
01:10:14.600 --> 01:10:18.120
You make us look good. we'll make you look good.

1163
01:10:19.180 --> 01:10:22.120
And maybe you get to keep the rest of your goddamn fingers.

1164
01:10:26.600 --> 01:10:30.380
I'm sorry that I killed your mayor.

1165
01:10:31.160 --> 01:10:32.700
I know you liked him a lot.

1166
01:10:33.960 --> 01:10:36.020
Though he did seem a bit of an a-hole.

1167
01:10:40.000 --> 01:10:40.440
Okay.

1168
01:10:42.380 --> 01:10:43.400
What do you say?

1169
01:10:45.160 --> 01:10:50.209
Well. uh. it isn't much trouble for him. 

1170
01:10:50.409 --> 01:10:54.785
Well I'm not much of a sheriff. but I'm all you've got.

1171
01:11:02.390 --> 01:11:05.370
Hey. Alex. what's the plan of the show?

1172
01:11:06.790 --> 01:11:09.370
I'm kind of liking Deputy.

1173
01:11:10.130 --> 01:11:10.690
Deputy.

1174
01:11:17.060 --> 01:11:17.900
Fuck yeah.

1175
01:11:19.320 --> 01:11:20.360
Come on. people!

1176
01:11:20.840 --> 01:11:21.960
This is the new normal!

1177
01:11:22.320 --> 01:11:23.720
It's gotta seem like an accident!

1178
01:11:24.020 --> 01:11:26.380
Like there wasn't a massacre here. you know?

1179
01:11:26.840 --> 01:11:27.420
Bring it in!

1180
01:11:27.480 --> 01:11:28.100
Bring it in!

1181
01:11:31.880 --> 01:11:33.700
Watch for blood splotches!

1182
01:11:34.940 --> 01:11:35.740
Cover them up!

1183
01:11:37.220 --> 01:11:38.340
Winter Wonderland!

1184
01:11:38.800 --> 01:11:40.160
Let's go for it. folks!

1185
01:11:40.860 --> 01:11:42.660
Pick a nice for our guests!

1186
01:11:43.740 --> 01:11:44.900
Bring it around!

1187
01:11:45.540 --> 01:11:46.500
Down there!

1188
01:11:47.140 --> 01:11:49.280
Look for any. uh. flutes on the trail!

1189
01:12:13.344 --> 01:12:17.910
I swear to God. I had no idea about killing Gunderson.

1190
01:12:18.430 --> 01:12:20.590
You believe that bullshit about the fishing rod?

1191
01:12:21.090 --> 01:12:24.430
Sorry. I'm not much of a fisherman. but yeah. I get your point.

1192
01:12:24.830 --> 01:12:26.570
And you tried to shoot me.

1193
01:12:27.410 --> 01:12:29.730
Yeah. I did shoot you. but I didn't kill you.

1194
01:12:30.290 --> 01:12:31.450
That's the important thing.

1195
01:12:32.250 --> 01:12:34.170
We're here together. both of us.

1196
01:12:36.730 --> 01:12:37.210
Alive.

1197
01:12:39.850 --> 01:12:42.930
Do you. uh. do you really think this is gonna work?

1198
01:12:45.430 --> 01:12:46.530
You're a bad man.

1199
01:12:47.690 --> 01:12:49.270
To my own detriment. to be sure.

1200
01:12:51.850 --> 01:12:55.210
I'd put a Benji on the lay.

1201
01:12:56.670 --> 01:12:59.530
Wait a minute. you're betting against us?

1202
01:13:04.120 --> 01:13:04.940
We're fucked. huh?

1203
01:13:07.780 --> 01:13:09.080
Let's get into character.

1204
01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:23.040
Okay. Hoagie.

1205
01:13:29.760 --> 01:13:31.800
Can you. can you. can you translate?

1206
01:13:34.080 --> 01:13:37.160
As you can see. the storm here was something else.

1207
01:13:37.660 --> 01:13:40.680
It knocked out phones. internet. self-service health.

1208
01:13:40.980 --> 01:13:42.660
You name it. it's done.

1209
01:13:43.240 --> 01:13:43.880
Howdy. y'all!

1210
01:13:45.200 --> 01:13:47.820
Oh. he's the interim. like I told you.

1211
01:13:48.580 --> 01:13:49.220
No. not yet.

1212
01:13:49.740 --> 01:13:51.300
He's. uh. not too bright.

1213
01:13:51.300 --> 01:13:53.280
Deputy Blaine. you know these folks?

1214
01:13:53.400 --> 01:13:59.220
You want to explain to them they can't come tearing through our county in a convoy like this without getting a greeting from the law?

1215
01:13:59.500 --> 01:14:02.760
Well. uh. this is actually Pastor Roy. my sheriff.

1216
01:14:03.240 --> 01:14:04.260
Oh. Pastor.

1217
01:14:04.500 --> 01:14:07.900
He's got a small parish just over yonder down near Everton.

1218
01:14:08.480 --> 01:14:09.820
What's his denomination?

1219
01:14:10.880 --> 01:14:11.400
Protestant.

1220
01:14:11.980 --> 01:14:12.800
Ain't that right?

1221
01:14:13.580 --> 01:14:14.840
I don't know what you guys are talking about.

1222
01:14:15.720 --> 01:14:16.720
Tell me. he's mad.

1223
01:14:17.440 --> 01:14:18.960
What's. what's he upset about?

1224
01:14:18.960 --> 01:14:23.880
I think. I think that he wants to go to a bank.

1225
01:14:24.980 --> 01:14:26.800
You can't go to a bank with cops.

1226
01:14:27.540 --> 01:14:29.220
Yeah. yeah. there's people.

1227
01:14:29.340 --> 01:14:30.020
It's true.

1228
01:14:32.460 --> 01:14:33.780
We'll make an exception.

1229
01:14:34.080 --> 01:14:34.920
Make an exception.

1230
01:14:35.060 --> 01:14:36.080
We'll give you an escort.

1231
01:14:36.880 --> 01:14:37.480
Follow us.

1232
01:14:37.580 --> 01:14:37.880
Let's go.

1233
01:14:42.160 --> 01:14:46.000
Okay. Deputy Blaine. let's take our guests a long way around.

1234
01:14:46.880 --> 01:14:49.180
Give him a little more time to fix up the bank.

1235
01:14:51.647 --> 01:14:56.669
How can these assholes get lost on a straight road !

1236
01:14:57.233 --> 01:15:01.061
Hey. yes. sir. right this way.

1237
01:15:01.261 --> 01:15:03.750
- This is it ?
- Yes. I'm certain all good.

1238
01:15:03.950 --> 01:15:07.399
- I know ...
- My money better be safe.

1239
01:15:14.580 --> 01:15:18.480
The driver was killed on impact. as was the bank manager and security guard.

1240
01:15:18.480 --> 01:15:19.460
I'll do that.

1241
01:15:19.520 --> 01:15:20.020
Thank you. sir.

1242
01:15:20.440 --> 01:15:22.300
Sheriff. do you mind if I show him the vault?

1243
01:15:22.640 --> 01:15:25.400
Yeah. the church has some papers and they're safe to pass it back.

1244
01:15:25.480 --> 01:15:26.520
Yeah. sure. go ahead.

1245
01:15:29.380 --> 01:15:31.000
The building's in fine shape.

1246
01:15:31.580 --> 01:15:33.860
Actually. it wasn't to load very well. excuse me.

1247
01:15:35.020 --> 01:15:40.940
As you can see. the vault is untouched. excuse me. pristine.

1248
01:15:41.840 --> 01:15:43.600
Whoa. the church has done well. huh?

1249
01:15:43.600 --> 01:15:50.150
It's a pretty color. huh?

1250
01:15:50.890 --> 01:15:52.554
Are you hungry?

1251
01:16:03.290 --> 01:16:05.370
Why did you invite them out for food?

1252
01:16:07.410 --> 01:16:12.290
I only know. like. four phrases in Japanese and I guess I panicked.

1253
01:16:15.870 --> 01:16:17.670
Is your boss enjoying the meatloaf?

1254
01:16:18.510 --> 01:16:19.830
What did you just call him?

1255
01:16:20.670 --> 01:16:22.590
This is divine.

1256
01:16:24.770 --> 01:16:26.650
Your English is very good. sir.

1257
01:16:27.590 --> 01:16:28.710
I watch a lot of friends.

1258
01:16:29.570 --> 01:16:30.730
Who's in for mimosas?

1259
01:16:32.730 --> 01:16:33.950
Should I make a toast?

1260
01:16:35.590 --> 01:16:36.170
Don't.

1261
01:16:36.950 --> 01:16:38.220
Excuse me. um...

1262
01:16:41.270 --> 01:16:44.110
I. uh. I'd like to propose a toast.

1263
01:16:44.110 --> 01:16:49.350
Um. you know. I'm. uh. what you might call a. uh. people person.

1264
01:16:49.650 --> 01:16:51.670
So this toast is to friendship.

1265
01:16:51.870 --> 01:16:54.490
I think it's important that I take credit for this event.

1266
01:16:54.870 --> 01:17:04.250
When I become the next Sheriff of Normal. there will be many more opportunities to come together and break bread. strengthening our link.

1267
01:17:04.829 --> 01:17:11.946
And. uh. with Pastor Oyuban and his friendly. friendly. um. congregation.

1268
01:17:11.946 --> 01:17:17.790
 I think this is a new chapter for our town and our happy arrangement.

1269
01:17:18.530 --> 01:17:23.961
So I'd like to say thank you for all your help and to many. 

1270
01:17:23.961 --> 01:17:32.510
many more years of friendly people helping other friendly people.

1271
01:20:47.150 --> 01:20:47.970
Damn it!

1272
01:21:27.730 --> 01:21:28.410
Sheriff!

1273
01:21:29.510 --> 01:21:30.470
Sheriff!

1274
01:21:38.790 --> 01:21:39.630
All friends now.

1275
01:21:48.870 --> 01:21:49.950
Any wood for pie?

1276
01:22:21.638 --> 01:22:22.520
You want to be Sheriff now?

1277
01:22:27.380 --> 01:22:27.940
Yeah?

1278
01:22:28.580 --> 01:22:29.020
Yeah. sure.

1279
01:22:36.980 --> 01:22:38.620
Thanks for taking care of me.

1280
01:22:41.000 --> 01:22:43.120
Oh. there's one other thing.

1281
01:22:46.840 --> 01:22:48.660
Here's that hundred on the leg.

1282
01:22:49.680 --> 01:22:50.420
Guess you won.

1283
01:22:52.480 --> 01:22:53.080
Ah!

1284
01:22:53.080 --> 01:22:54.260
Can I have that pie back?

1285
01:23:10.680 --> 01:23:14.751
ONE MONTH LATER

1286
01:23:26.460 --> 01:23:28.360
I prefer the weather here.

1287
01:23:28.600 --> 01:23:29.100
It's warm.

1288
01:23:29.340 --> 01:23:30.360
Don't miss the cold.

1289
01:23:31.020 --> 01:23:34.240
Oh. and I picked up an interim deputy along the way.

1290
01:23:34.840 --> 01:23:36.380
People are pretty much the same.

1291
01:23:36.940 --> 01:23:38.100
Then again. not.

1292
01:23:38.800 --> 01:23:43.340
All things considered. though. I'm in a better place.

1293
01:23:44.560 --> 01:23:49.160
As for the town of Normal. well. I left it as I found it. you could say.

1294
01:23:50.720 --> 01:23:52.460
I mean. that's the job. isn't it?

1295
01:23:53.720 --> 01:23:55.800
Besides. I'm never looking for trouble.

1296
01:23:56.600 --> 01:23:59.040
If it wants you. it'll find you on its own.

1297
01:24:00.080 --> 01:24:03.040
And it can be hard to shake once it does.

1298
01:24:06.370 --> 01:24:08.590
Well. thanks for listening. Penny.

1299
01:24:09.030 --> 01:24:09.390
Bye.

1300
01:24:09.990 --> 01:24:11.430
Hi. Ulysses.

1301
01:24:12.490 --> 01:24:13.790
Hey. Penny.
